&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own small to medium OutSystems low-code solutions and features from design through production with minimal guidance. Improve solution quality and team practices, mentor Application Developer 1 teammates through clear documentation, thoughtful reviews, and knowledge sharing as appropriate, and participate in the weekly on-call rotation handling a broader set of incidents. Influence spans the solution or feature area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead implementation of OutSystems Reactive Web applications and workflow automation features or components in Service Studio, break down work, estimate, and drive to delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thoughtful reviews of applications, automations, and configurations for clarity, maintainability, and correctness, raise the bar on testing and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support production solutions, lead incident triage for the team&#39;s area using execution history, logs, and telemetry, and document findings and fixes in the team wiki and repository READMEs where appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to incident reviews and follow-ups that reduce repeat issues, including improvements to error handling, alerts, and resilience patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply sound solution architecture principles in everyday work, guide Application Developer 1 teammates on the basics, and improve observability, reliability, security, and privacy baselines for owned solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product and design on solution shaping, highlight risks and tradeoffs such as platform licensing, performance, and governance constraints, and propose pragmatic alternatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to team design documents, review designs for adjacent solutions or integrations, and champion documentation quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and deliver incremental refactors that reduce toil, improve performance, and increase reuse across low-code solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in daily standups and core team ceremonies, communicate status and risks early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS REQUIRED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year minimum required. Candidates should be able to demonstrate hands-on OutSystems development capability through prior work, portfolio projects, OutSystems certification, technical assessment, or production support experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, mentoring, and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to troubleshoot issues systematically using logs, execution history, data review, reproduction steps, and clear root-cause analysis.&lt;/li

